[4] Maniema province: Kindu Airport response
Date: Thu 4 Oct 2018
Source: Media Congo [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://www.mediacongo.net/article-actualite-43010_lutte_contre_ebola_des_dispositifs_d_hygiene_installes_a_l_aeroport_de_kindu.html


Health authorities are increasingly reinforcing the surveillance measures of the current epidemic to protect the population against its spread. Surveillance has been strengthened at entry points in Maniema province. The Health and Safety Brigade of the Provincial Health Division installed hygiene devices against Ebola fever at Kindu National Airport.

According to Damien Katenda, quoted by the Congolese News Agency, the installation of handwashing kits and of thermo-temperature monitoring is part of the fight against this disease in Maniema, one of the country's high-risk provinces because of travelers from infected provinces, including South Kivu, North Kivu, and the former Eastern province. Damien Katenda urged the workers at Kindu airport to make travelers aware of the strict rules of hygiene.

[byline: Blandine Lusimana]

